***************************************************************************************

The function of this plugin is to provide REST service for:
 - acquiring the list of options for jira select list customfields in given context
 - adding new options to field options list
 - disabling options
 - enabling disabled options
 the list of customfields, which dictionaries are exposed by plugin REST service is
 stored in plugin setting. Settings are available at plugin configuration page

REST API endpoints:

for GET fieldOptionsRequest to acquire the options of customfild in given context:
http://{jira base URL}/rest/cfoptchange/1.0/options?fieldKey={key}
        &projectKey={key}&issueTypeId={id}

for POST fieldOptionsRequest to append new option to options of customfield in given context:
http://{jira base URL}/rest/cfoptchange/1.0/options?fieldKey={key}
        &projectKey={key}&issueTypeId={id}&newOption{value}

test classes, inherited from skeleton plugin in
    src\test\java\ut\HCBplugins\rest\CfOptChangeTest.java
are commented out

response looks like:
{
    "fieldKey": "customfield_10008",
    "projectKey": "TES",
    "issueTypeId": "10000",
    "newOption": "not provided",
    "action": "NOT_RECOGNIZED",
    "fieldName": "MultiSelectField",
    "projectName": "tes",
    "fieldConfigName": "Default Configuration for MultiSelectField",
    "fieldOptions": [
        "value1",
        "value2",
        "some disabled value",
        "one more value"
    ],
    "isDisabled": {
        "value2": false,
        "value1": false,
        "one more value": false,
        "some disabled value": true
    },
    "optionIds": {
        "10003": "value1",
        "10004": "value2",
        "10005": "some disabled value",
        "10006": "one more value"
    },
    "success": "true"
}

if there are two or more options with similar values it may look ambiguous
which one is disabled




